-- Aflac Plans Further Cuts to Europe Financial-Firm Investments
-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 2012-02-01T14:57:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/aflac-plans-further-cuts-to-europe-financial-firm-investments.html
Aflac Inc. (AFL) , the world’s largest
supplemental health insurer, said it will continue to cut its
investments in European financial firms.  “Clearly the financials represent the greatest challenge
with respect to the situation in  Europe ,” Chief Investment
Officer Eric Kirsch said today in a conference call with
analysts. “I felt it was necessary to have a strategy to
continue to reduce these exposures.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
